"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "3015: Holy Spirit, divinity of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3015",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Holy Spirit's attributes and activities are always those of God. The titles used of the Holy Spirit identify him as part of the triune nature of the divine being.</p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit possesses the attributes of God</h2>\n<h3>He is present everywhere</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:7-Ps139:8\">PSA 139:7–139:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:17\">JHN 14:17</a></p>\n<h3>He knows all things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:13\">ISA 40:13</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13\">JHN 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:10-1Cor2:11\">1CO 2:10–2:11</a></p>\n<h3>He has infinite power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:6\">ZEC 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a></p>\n<h3>He is eternal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16\">JHN 14:16</a></p>\n<h3>He is unique</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:6\">EPH 4:4–4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4\">1CO 12:4</a></p>\n<h3>He is holy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:5\">ROM 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">1CO 6:19</a> <em>The Christian's body is also holy because it is the place where God dwells by his Spirit</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:6\">2CO 6:6</a>EPH <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:13\">1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:8\">HEB 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:12\">1PE 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:21\">2PE 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:20\">JUD 1:20</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit performs divine works</h2>\n<h3>He creates</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:30\">PSA 104:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:2\">GEN 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:13\">JOB 26:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:4\">JOB 33:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a></p>\n<h3>He gives life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:14\">EZK 37:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:7\">GEN 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:2\">ROM 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:11\">ROM 8:11</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is identified with the person and activity of the Godhead</h2>\n<h3><code>Holy Spirit'' and</code>God'' are used interchangeably</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:4\">ACT 5:3–5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is called ``Lord''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It is possible to blaspheme the Spirit</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:32\">MAT 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:29\">MRK 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:10\">LUK 12:10</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is sent by the Father and the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:14-John16:15\">JHN 16:14–16:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is identified with the Father and the Son</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a> <em>in commissioning</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a> <em>in benediction</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a> <em>in access to God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1-1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is given divine titles</h2>\n<h3>The Spirit of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:1\">2CH 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:3\">EXO 31:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:2\">NUM 24:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:10\">1SA 10:10</a> <em>Saul prophesies at Gibeah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:20\">1SA 19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:20\">2CH 24:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:24\">EZK 11:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16\">MAT 3:16</a> <em>at Jesus Christ's baptism</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:11\">1CO 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14\">1CO 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:14\">1PE 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:10\">JDG 3:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:34\">JDG 6:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13-1Sam16:14\">1SA 16:13–16:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:2\">2SA 23:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:24\">1KI 22:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:16\">2KI 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:23\">2CH 18:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:2\">ISA 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:14\">ISA 63:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:5\">EZK 11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:1\">EZK 37:1</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of the Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18\">LUK 4:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17\">2CO 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">ROM 8:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:19\">PHP 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:11\">1PE 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of Jesus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:7\">ACT 16:7</a></p>",
